{
  "texts": [
    "This framework aims to provide personalized assistance and transparent decisionmaking.In the realm of computer vision and natural language processing, Mao et al. [36] proposed Agent-Driver, which introduces a versatile tool library and cognitive memory to integrate human-like intelligence into autonomous driving systems.",
    "By processing sensory data x sensory, Agent-Driver generates actions a for autonomous vehicles, demonstrating superior interpretability and few-shot learning ability.",
    "Mao et al. [37] also presented GPT-Driver, which reformulates motion planning as a language modeling problem.",
    "By representing scenario descriptions x scenario as language tokens, GPT-Driver generates trajectories a traj, identifies notable objects a obj, and predicts potential effects a effect through a prompting-reasoningfinetuning strategy.Other notable contributions include TrafficGPT by Zhang et al. [34], which empowers LLMs with the ability to analyze traffic information x traffic and provide driving suggestions a suggest and tool choices a tool; DriveLLM by Cui et al.",
    "[35], which integrates LLMs with existing autonomous driving stacks for commonsense reasoning in decision-making; SayNav by Rajvanshi et al. [39], which utilizes a 3D scene graph prompt x graph to ground LLMs for generating highlevel navigation plans a nav; and the work by Tanahashi et al."
  ]
}